    "body": "This is how Parity/OpenEthereum used to work. In our code we call it \"gas bailout\", and it specifically prevents failure in such cases. I introduced this in this PR: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/pull/2485 when trying to make `trace_call` behave the same as OpenEthereum.\r\n\r\nSince there is no specification for how `trace_call` has to behave in this case, do we just remove gasBailout in this case? Nethermind is now the \"gold standard\" ?",
